Adamu Garba has taken his Twitter page to express his will to join in the race for 2023 presidency. In his statement, he explains he’ll be declaring his aspiration for the Office of the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria today, April 16 2022. He seeks the assistance of Nigerians to do it for our dear country. He ends his tweet with prayers.
Ahead of the 2023 presidency, it would be a total of eight presidential aspirants who has declared their aspiration for the position of the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria if he declares today.
Adamu Garba tweets “I will be declaring to aspire for the office of the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria on 16 April 2022 insha Allahu. Let’s do this for our country, guys. May Allah, the Guarantor, Guardian and Grantor of Power and Authority see us through”
